## Pass 2: Presentation Strategy

### 2.1 Framework (Choose ONE)

| Framework | Structure | Best When |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| **Pyramid** | Recommendation ‚Üí Arguments ‚Üí Evidence ‚Üí Action | Answer-first |
| **SCR** | Situation ‚Üí Complication ‚Üí Resolution ‚Üí Implications | Problem-solving |
| **Transformation** | Old World ‚Üí Disruption ‚Üí New World ‚Üí Imperatives | Before/after |
| **Countdown** | Stakes ‚Üí Deadline ‚Üí Readiness ‚Üí Action | Urgency |
| **Evidence Cascade** | Foundation ‚Üí Build ‚Üí Conclusion ‚Üí Action | Data-rich case |

**Selection**: [Framework] ‚Äî [Why]

### 2.2 Opening Hook (Choose ONE)

| Hook | Pattern |
|------|---------|
| **Number** | Lead with striking statistic |
| **Question** | Provocative question |
| **Stakes** | Quantified risk/opportunity |
| **Shift** | "Everything changed when..." |
| **Contrast** | "While X... Y..." |

**Selection**: [Hook] ‚Äî [Why]

### 2.3 Closing (Choose ONE)

| Technique | Pattern |
|-----------|---------|
| **Callback** | Return to opening |
| **Choice** | "Two paths..." |
| **Imperative** | Direct call to action |
| **Timeline** | "By [date]..." |
| **Question** | What matters most |

**Selection**: [Technique] ‚Äî [Why]

---

## Pass 3: Slide Architecture

### 3.1 Slide Types

**Use these types (aligned with P4 JSON schema):**

| Type | Purpose | P4 JSON Value |
|------|---------|---------------|
| **Title** | Opening slide; centered title + subtitle | `title` |
| **Section** | Section divider; transition between topics | `section` |
| **Content** | Text-focused; bullets, paragraphs, callouts | `content` |
| **Chart** | Data visualization-led; chart dominates | `chart` |
| **Comparison** | Side-by-side analysis; two-column or table | `comparison` |
| **Action** | Recommendations; WHO does WHAT by WHEN | `action` |
| **Closing** | Final slide; callback or call-to-action | `closing` |

### 3.2 Block Allocation

**Use target from 1.4. Merge/drop blocks to hit range.**

**Pyramid:**
| Block | Type | Slides | Flexible? |
|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| Opening | title | 1 | Fixed |
| Recommendation | action | 1 | Fixed |
| Argument 1‚Äì3 | content / chart | 1‚Äì2 each | Merge/drop |
| Implications | content | 1‚Äì2 | Merge |
| Action | action | 1 | Fixed |
| Close | closing | 1 | Fixed |

**SCR:**
| Block | Type | Slides | Flexible? |
|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| Opening | title | 1 | Fixed |
| Situation | section + content | 1‚Äì2 | Condense |
| Complication | content / chart | 1‚Äì2 | Condense |
| Resolution | content / chart | 2‚Äì3 | Scale |
| Implications | content | 1‚Äì2 | Merge |
| Action | action | 1 | Fixed |
| Close | closing | 1 | Fixed |

**Transformation:**
| Block | Type | Slides | Flexible? |
|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| Opening | title | 1 | Fixed |
| Old World | section + content | 1‚Äì2 | Condense |
| Disruption | chart / content | 1‚Äì2 | Scale |
| New World | content / chart | 2‚Äì3 | Scale |
| Imperatives | action | 1 | Fixed |
| Close | closing | 1 | Fixed |

**Countdown:**
| Block | Type | Slides | Flexible? |
|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| Opening | title | 1 | Fixed |
| Stakes | chart / content | 1 | Fixed |
| Deadline | content | 1 | Fixed |
| Ready/Not Ready | comparison / chart | 2‚Äì4 | Scale |
| Reckoning | content | 1 | Merge |
| Action | action | 1 | Fixed |
| Close | closing | 1 | Fixed |

**Evidence Cascade:**
| Block | Type | Slides | Flexible? |
|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| Opening | title | 1 | Fixed |
| Foundation | section + content | 1‚Äì2 | Condense |
| Layers 1‚Äì3 | chart / content | 1‚Äì2 each | Scale/drop |
| Synthesis | content | 1 | Fixed |
| Action | action | 1 | Fixed |
| Close | closing | 1 | Fixed |

**Planned count**: [#]

### 3.3 Slide Assignment

| # | Title (Draft) | Type | Layout Template | Content Blocks | Source |
|---|---------------|------|-----------------|----------------|--------|
| 1 | | title | title_centered | ‚Äî | |
| 2 | | | | | |
| ... | | | | | |

**Layout Template Options** (must match P4 schema):
- `title_centered` ‚Äî Opening slide, centered title + subtitle
- `section_divider` ‚Äî Section transition, large title only
- `title_content` ‚Äî Title + full-width bullets/text
- `content_visual_split` ‚Äî 60/40 split, text left, visual right
- `visual_content_split` ‚Äî 40/60 split, visual left, text right
- `chart_focus` ‚Äî Title + large chart area (80% height)
- `two_column` ‚Äî 50/50 split for comparisons
- `three_column` ‚Äî 33/33/33 split for multiple items
- `callout_quote` ‚Äî Large centered quote with attribution
- `action_items` ‚Äî Title + numbered action items
- `appendix` ‚Äî Smaller title, dense content

**Content Block Types** (for P4 JSON generation):
- `bullet_list` ‚Äî Unordered list (3-5 bullets)
- `numbered_list` ‚Äî Ordered list (steps, rankings)
- `paragraph` ‚Äî Prose text block
- `callout_box` ‚Äî Highlighted insight or quote
- `data_point` ‚Äî Large number + label
- `table` ‚Äî Structured comparison grid

### 3.4 Transitions

| From ‚Üí To | Bridge |
|-----------|--------|
| 1 ‚Üí 2 | |
| 2 ‚Üí 3 | |

### 3.5 Appendix Strategy

**Rule**: If removing doesn't break the story ‚Üí appendix.

| ID | Topic | Triggered By |
|----|-------|--------------|
| A | | "[Question]" |
| B | | "[Question]" |

### 3.6 Chart Data Specification

**For each chart, provide structured data for P4/P5 generation:**

| Slide # | Chart Type | Data Labels | Data Values | Series Name | Y-Axis Label |
|---------|------------|-------------|-------------|-------------|--------------|
| | bar_horizontal | ["Label A", "Label B", "Label C"] | [45, 32, 28] | "Revenue ($M)" | "Amount" |
| | line | ["2020", "2021", "2022", "2023"] | [12, 18, 24, 31] | "Growth Rate" | "Percentage" |
| | pie | ["Segment A", "Segment B", "Segment C"] | [55, 30, 15] | "Market Share" | ‚Äî |

**Multi-series charts**:
```
Slide #: [X]
Chart Type: line (multi-series)
X-Axis Labels: ["Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"]
Series:
  - Name: "Product A", Values: [10, 15, 12, 18]
  - Name: "Product B", Values: [8, 12, 14, 16]
Y-Axis Label: "Units Sold"
```

**Data extraction rule**: All values must come from the executive summary or Stage 1 research. If exact values are unavailable, note `[VALUE NEEDED]` and flag for user input.

