## Pass 4: Draft

### Slide Format
```
---
## Slide [#]: [Assertion Title]

**Type**: [title / section / content / chart / comparison / action / closing]

**Layout Template**: [title_centered / section_divider / title_content / content_visual_split / visual_content_split / chart_focus / two_column / action_items / appendix]

**Content Blocks**:
- [block_type]: [content]
  - bullet_list: ["Item 1", "Item 2", "Item 3"]
  - paragraph: "Full sentence text..."
  - data_point: { value: "47%", label: "Market Share" }
  - callout_box: "Key insight text..."

**Visual Element** (if applicable):
- Chart Type: [bar_vertical / bar_horizontal / line / pie / donut]
- Chart Title: "[Action title - assertion, not label]"
- Data: { labels: [...], values: [...], series_name: "..." }
- Alt Text: "[Accessibility description]"

**Footnotes**:
- Source: "[Abbrev, location]"
- Date caveat: "Data as of [date]"

**Speaker Notes** (FULL text for PPTX export):
```
[TRANSITION]: [Bridge from previous slide - what connects these ideas]

[Main talking points - write as you would speak, 3-5 sentences]:
- Point 1: [Full sentence to speak]
- Point 2: [Full sentence to speak]

[KEY POINT]: [Emphasize this - slow down]

[CONFIDENCE FLAG]: [If Low/Speculative: "Note that this projection is based on limited data..."]

[OBJECTION PREEMPT]: [If anticipated pushback: "You may wonder about X‚Äîhere's why..."]

[Bridge to next]: [Transition phrase to next slide]
```

**GT Connection**: [How this supports governing thought]

**Traceability**: F-IDs: [F1, F2] | Q-Refs: [Q1, Q1.2]
---
```

[Draft all slides]

