## Pass 5: Quality Tests

### 5.1 Flow Test

| Criterion | ‚úì/‚úó |
|-----------|-----|
| Hooks immediately? | |
| Logical progression? | |
| Transitions explicit in speaker notes? | |
| Conclusion earned? | |

### 5.2 One-Idea Test

| Slide # | Core Idea | Competing? | ‚úì/‚úó |
|---------|-----------|------------|-----|
| | | | |

### 5.3 Evidence Test

| Slide # | Claims | In Summary? | ‚úì/‚úó |
|---------|--------|-------------|-----|
| | | | |

### 5.4 Action Test

| Criterion | ‚úì/‚úó |
|-----------|-----|
| Clear Action slide (type: action)? | |
| WHO/WHAT/WHEN specified? | |
| Urgency clear? | |

### 5.5 Headline Test

List titles in sequence:
1.
2.
3.
...

| Criterion | ‚úì/‚úó |
|-----------|-----|
| Titles alone tell complete story? | |
| Stranger understands "so what"? | |
| Governing thought supported? | |
| Reviewable without slide content? | |

**If headlines don't tell the story, rewrite before proceeding.**

### 5.6 Red Thread Test

| # | Title | GT Connection | ‚úì/‚úó |
|---|-------|---------------|-----|
| 1 | | | |
| 2 | | | |

**No clear connection ‚Üí restructure, appendix, or cut.**

### 5.7 P4/P5 Readiness Test (NEW)

| Criterion | ‚úì/‚úó |
|-----------|-----|
| All slide types use P4 vocabulary? (title/section/content/chart/comparison/action/closing) | |
| Layout templates specified for all slides? | |
| Content block types specified? (bullet_list/paragraph/data_point/callout_box/table) | |
| Chart data includes labels, values, and series names? | |
| Full speaker notes provided (not summaries)? | |
| Alt text provided for all visual elements? | |
| Confidence flags included in speaker notes for Low/Speculative claims? | |
| Traceability (F-IDs, Q-Refs) maintained for all slides? | |

**If any P4/P5 readiness checks fail, fix before proceeding to Pass 6.**

