### 6.1 Failures & Fixes

| Test | Issue | Fix |
|------|-------|-----|
| | | |

### 6.2 Polish Checklist

**Titles**:
- [ ] All titles are assertions
- [ ] All chart titles are assertions
- [ ] Headlines alone tell story

**Speaker Notes**:
- [ ] Full text provided (not summaries)
- [ ] Say what to SPEAK
- [ ] Pacing cues included ([TRANSITION], [KEY POINT], [PAUSE])
- [ ] Transitions explicit
- [ ] Objections preempted
- [ ] Confidence flags for Low/Speculative claims

**Footnotes & Visuals**:
- [ ] Sources noted with abbreviations
- [ ] Date caveats where needed
- [ ] Visuals varied
- [ ] Charts have action titles
- [ ] Alt text for accessibility

**P4/P5 Readiness**:
- [ ] Slide types match P4 vocabulary
- [ ] Layout templates specified
- [ ] Content block types specified
- [ ] Chart data tables complete (labels, values, series)
- [ ] Traceability preserved (F-IDs, Q-Refs)

### 6.3 Count Check

| Target | Actual | Status |
|--------|--------|--------|
| | | |

### 6.4 Appendix Check

- [ ] All objections (1.6) have backup slides
- [ ] Triggers documented

